description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PREVIOUS APPLICANTS NEED NOT APPLY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rotational Occupational Therapist - Band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for Occupational therapists with excellent communication skills to join our expanding Occupational Therapy team at Lewisham and Greenwich NHS Trust. You will be based at University Hospital Lewisham or a community site within Lewisham. You will have an excellent opportunity to develop your knowledge and skills and to further your career in a Band 6 post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The posts are for qualified Occupational Therapist with experience at Band 5 or Band 6 level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A professional attitude is essential along with the skills to work in a busy setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Department&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An excellent working environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A supportive management structure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A positive and well-established appraisal and development system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Encouragement to develop clinical skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rotations into 10 different speciality areas: Emergency Department, Fraility, Stroke, Care of the Elderly, Medicine, Trauma and Orthopaedic, Social Services, Community Adult Therapy Team, Community Neuro Team, Intermediate Care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clinical leadership is provided through an established structure of professional lead occupational therapist and senior OT team leads, regular in-service training, clinical supervision and good peer group support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Candidates&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential experience required:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Post-graduate clinical experience working as a Band 5 Occupational Therapist&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evidence of participation in In-service training and Personal CPD&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HCPC registration and RCOT/BAOT membership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates must have a professional, enthusiastic, friendly and flexible approach&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working days and or shift patterns will be agreed by the line manager to meet the needs of the service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits will be available on request to shortlisted candidates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PREVIOUS APPLICANTS NEED NOT APPLY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Emma Tilley, Lead Occupational Therapist - emma.tilley1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
